WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
So today, I think what we're going to tackle over the course of a couple weeks

00:00:06.640 --> 00:00:10.400
is looking at really practical ways that people can use GenAI.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.920
And I think where we're going to start is with Copilot and taking a look at that, right?

00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:32.720
The main thing that I'm hearing from groups and people in leadership is how do we embrace this

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:40.160
tool to help with the migration and transition to more programmers in the open source space,

00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:45.919
and specifically in the drug development space, using R for late-stage clinical trials.

00:00:45.919 --> 00:00:50.000
And so I think there's some stuff there where this can help with some of that.

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:54.880
It's not perfect, but I do think there's a piece to this that's pretty cool.

00:00:54.880 --> 00:01:01.439
So we're going to show some of this today on how people can use Copilot to create some shiny apps.

00:01:03.040 --> 00:01:04.080
I love it.

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:08.879
All right, so why don't you open up our studio?

